problem.markdown:
>>What is the main purpose of early stopping?<<

( ) It is a standard way to train a model faster. {{ With early stopping, the training process will stop sooner than using a large number of epochs, but this is not the main purpose of it. }}
(x) It regularizes the model by not allowing the model parameters to memorize and overfit. 
( ) It is a way to stop the training process when the model underfits the data, so that we can adjust the hyperparameters quickly.  {{This is not the main purpose of early stopping.}}
( ) It stops the learning process before it becomes unstable and leads to forgetting the representations. {{Early stopping does not address the stability of the learning process. Ensuring stability is the role of the optimizer, as you will see in the following sections of this course.}}

